AFFECTED SYSTEM AGREEMENT
THIS AFFECTED SYSTEM AGREEMENT (the "Agreement") is made effective as of the 28 day of September, 2023 (the "Effective Date") by and between Southern Power Company ("SPC"), a corporation organized and existing under the laws of the State of Delaware, and Old Hayneville Solar, LLC ("Generator"), a limited liability company organized and existing under the laws of Delaware (hereinafter each referred to individually as a "Party" and collectively as "the Parties").
WITNESSETH:
WHEREAS, the Generator intends to own and operate a 80 MW generating facility located in Montgomery County, Alabama (herein referred to as "Generator Facilities");
WHEREAS, the Generator has requested to interconnect its Generator Facilities into transmission facilities owned by Alabama Power Company ("APC");
WHEREAS, APC owns certain transmission lines and facilities in Alabama ("APC System");
WHEREAS, in accordance with open-access transmission requirements, APC has conducted required facilities and system impact assessments, and has coordinated with potentially affected systems, including systems owned and operated by Southern Power Company potentially would be affected by the interconnection of the Generator Facility;
WHEREAS, APC identified that, in addition to facilities and equipment necessary to physically and electrically interconnect the Generator Facility to the APC System, electric system facilities owned by SPC potentially would be affected by the interconnection of the Generator Facility (the "Affected System");
WHEREAS, SPC assessed the potential Affected System impacts and has determined that the interconnection of the Generator Facility will have certain negative effects on the Affected System (each such effect, an "Adverse System Impact") and that additions, modifications, and upgrades must be made to SPC's Interconnection Customer Owned Interconnection Facilities to accommodate the Generator interconnection request so as to avoid compromising the safety and reliability of the electric system, as further identified within that certain Facilities Study (as defined below);
WHEREAS, SPC has requested and the Generator has agreed to enter into this Agreement for the purpose of facilitating the interconnection of the Generator to the APC System ("Affected System Upgrades") and for no other purpose;
WHEREAS, the Generator desires to provide, and SPC desires to obtain, payment to fully compensate SPC for all Affected System Upgrades required by SPC to accommodate the Generator in connection with its interconnection to the APC System; NOW, THEREFORE, for and in consideration of the premises, the mutual promises and agreements set forth herein and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt, sufficiency and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, the Generator and SPC each intending to be legally bound, hereby agree as follows:
ARTICLE I - DEFINITIONS
Whenever used in this Agreement and Appendices hereto, the following terms shall have the following meanings:
1.1 Adverse System Impact - the negative effects due to technical or operational limits on conductors or equipment being exceeded that may compromise the safety and reliability of the electric system.
1.2 Agreement - this Affected System Agreement made effective as of the Effective Date between the Generator and SPC, including all appendices hereto, as amended or modified in accordance with the terms of this Agreement and which are made a part hereof for all purposes.
1.3 Affected System - SPC owned interconnection facilities adversely affected by the Generator Facility's interconnection and interconnection requests between the Generator and APC.
1.4 Affected System Upgrades - additions, modifications, and upgrades to the SPC System required in order to accommodate the Generator Interconnection Request, as described herein.
1.5 Applicable Laws and Regulations - Shall mean all duly promulgated applicable federal, state and local laws, regulations, rules, ordinances, codes, decrees, judgments, directives, or judicial or administrative orders, permits and other duly authorized actions of any Governmental Authority.
1.6 Event of Default - has the meaning set forth in Section 5.2.
1.7 Effective Date - the date specified in Section 1.2, above.
1.8 Facilities Study - The study performed by Southern Company Services ("SCS") that identifies and analyzes the impact on the APC System and potentially affected third party systems, including those electric systems owned by existing interconnected generators, such as the SPC System, and provides remedial measures to mitigate the adverse impacts.
1.9 Force Majeure - the occurrence or non-occurrence of any act or event that could not reasonably have been expected and avoided by the exercise of due diligence and foresight and such act or event is beyond the reasonable control of the affected Party relying thereon as justification for its not performing an obligation or complying with any condition required of such Party (or such Party's contractors, subcontractors or agents) pursuant to this Agreement.
1.10 Generator Facilities - the electric generation facility to be constructed by the Generator on the Generator Facilities Site, including generation and related facilities.
1.11 Generator Facilities Site - the tract of land located in Montgomery County upon which the Generator Facilities are to be constructed.
1.12 Generator Interconnection Request - the Generator's request to interconnect into APC's System.
1.13 Governmental Authority - any local, state, regional, federal or national administrative, legal, judicial or executive agency, commission, department or other governmental entity having jurisdiction over the Parties, their respective facilities, or respective services they provide.
1.14 Good Utility Practice - any of the practices, methods and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric utility industry during the relevant time period, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with good business practices, reliability, safety and expedition. Good Utility Practice is not intended to be limited to the optimum practice, method or act to the exclusion of all others, but rather to be a spectrum of acceptable practices, methods or acts generally accepted in the region.
1.15 In-Service Date - the date upon which the Generator reasonably expects it will reach commercial operation, pursuant to the Generator Interconnection Request. The In Service Date for this project is currently projected to be 6/2/2025.
1.16 Lost Revenue - the estimated lost net revenue, lost profits and other costs incurred by SPC caused by an applicable outage or disconnection of the Affected System. Lost Revenue shall include any revenues that SPC would have received, net of associated fuel costs, whether from a wholesale market sale or pursuant to an applicable offtake agreement, and any fines, penalties, or other costs SPC becomes liable for due to the applicable outage (including any offtake agreement charges or penalties for unavailiability).
1.17 Party - Shall mean a party to this Agreement, as named in the preamble above, and "Parties" shall mean both such parties.
1.18 Transmission Provider - Shall mean the entity that operates the Affected System. For purposes of this Agreement, the Transmission Provider shall mean Alabama Power Company.
ARTICLE II - TERM OF AGREEMENT
2.1 Term - This Agreement shall bind the Parties as of the Effective Date, subject to and in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement, and shall remain in effect until the Affected System Upgrades have been constructed and placed into service and all payments have been made, unless earlier terminated pursuant to the terms hereof.
2.2 Opportunity To Cure Prior to Termination - No Party hereto shall seek to terminate this Agreement as a result of a material breach by the other Party hereto without providing the breaching Party at least fifteen (15) calendar days' advance written notice and at least thirty (30) days to cure such breach.
ARTICLE III - AFFECTED SYSTEM UPGRADES
3.1 Upgrades - SPC shall upgrade the SPC System in accordance with this Agreement and consistent with Good Utility Practice. SPC shall own all of the Affected System Upgrades.
3.2 Affected System Upgrades
3.2.1 SPC and/or its affiliated service company, Southern Company Services, Inc. ("SCS") shall design, procure, construct, install, and SPC shall own the Affected System Upgrades necessary to accommodate the Generator's Generator Interconnection Request as provided in Appendix A.
3.2.2 The Generator shall reimburse SPC for all costs of the design, procurement, construction, including Lost Revenues incurred during any outage(s) that SPC determines are reasonably necessary to install the Affected System Upgrades in accordance with Section 3.2.3, and maintenance of the Affected System Upgrades pursuant to Section 3.2.1, for completing the design, procurement, construction and installation and all related costs and expenses, including but not limited to, all legal, administrative, accounting and other costs that SPC would not have incurred but for the Generator's Generator Interconnection Request ("SPC Work"), including the legal costs of establishing this agreement and administering any associated regulatory approvals or submissions relating thereto.1 SPC shall bill the Generator for such costs in accordance with Section 3.2.3 and Section 7.1, and Generator shall be responsible for payment in accordance with Section 3.2.3 and Section 7.1 of this Agreement for all SPC Work. SPC shall perform all SPC Work in accordance with Good Utility Practice.
3.2.3 In the event that the Generator is required to reimburse the SPC for Lost Revenues pursuant to this Section 3.2.2, within twenty (20) calendar days following the conclusion of the outage or disconnection and subsequent re-energization of the Affected System, SPC will provide the the Generator with an invoice specifying the total amount of Lost Revenue during the outage period, along with commercially reasonable supporting documentation. Such documentation shall include the estimated lost energy production (in megawatt-hours "MWh" per hour) for each day of the outage period and any other payments or remedies SPC is required to make or do pursuant to any effective agreement, market rules, or other applicable law associated with the outage(s). The Generator will have the opportunity to review the invoice and supporting documentation, and to submit written inquiries to SPC within ten (10) calendar days of receiving such invoice, who shall provide written responses to any inquiries received from the Generator concerning the invoice and supporting documentation within ten (10) calendar days of receiving such inquiries. Payment by Generator to SPC for Lost Revenues and other amounts due and owing pursuant to Section 3.2 shall be in accordance with Section 7.1.
3.3 Right to Cost Information - Subject to the confidentiality requirements contained within this Agreement, the Generator shall have the right to receive all information about the costs under this Agreement as it shall reasonably request with respect to the SPC Work; provided, however that SPC need not produce any such information in a form other than that maintained in the ordinary course of its business in accordance with applicable accounting regulations.
3.3.1 Availability of Records - For a period of 180 days after the Generator's receipt of any invoice or adjustment to any invoice from SPC for charges incurred under this Agreement, the Generator, or any third party representative of the Generator reasonably acceptable to SPC, shall have the right upon at least five (5) Business Days prior written notice, at the Generator's sole expense and during normal working hours, to examine copies of the records of SPC to the extent reasonably necessary to verify the accuracy of any charge(s) related to such invoice. Notwithstanding the foregoing, SPC shall only be obligated to provide such records to the extent legally permissible and so long as the Generator and any third party representative of the Generator agree to maintain the confidentiality of any records provided by SPC with respect to such audit. In the event an audit is requested by the Generator with respect to such records and those records cannot be disclosed to the Generator as a result of an existing SPC confidentiality obligation, then to the extent legally permissible, the Parties shall select an independent auditor to perform the audit consistent with the Parties' rights under this Agreement and with such confidentiality arrangements as may be required. The Generator, as the Party requesting the audit, shall pay all costs for any independent auditor retained in accordance with this Section. Any audit authorized by this provision shall be performed at the offices where such accounts and records are maintained and shall be limited to those portions of such accounts and records that specifically relate to each Party's performance and satisfaction of its obligations under this Agreement.
3.3.2 If an audit by a Party determines that an overpayment or an underpayment has occurred, a notice of such discrepancy shall be given to the other Party together with the associated records from the audit which support such determination.
ARTICLE IV - FACILITY AND EQUIPMENT DESIGN AND CONSTRUCTION
4.1 The Affected System Upgrades shall meet all requirements of applicable safety and/or engineering codes, and further, shall meet all requirements of any Government Authority having jurisdiction over such matters. Affected System Upgrades are consistent with operational control, reliability and/or safety standards or requirements of the SPC System.
ARTICLE V - RIGHT TO TERMINATE
5.1 Right of the Generator to Terminate
5.1.1 Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, Generator may decide not to interconnect the Generator Facility with the Transmission Provider as contemplated by this Agreement and may terminate this Agreement by written notice to SPC prior to the In-Service Date; provided, however, that such termination is not effective until the Generator pays to SPC, pursuant to Section 7.1, all costs and fees that SPC has incurred or will incur prior to or due to the termination for the SPC Work under this Agreement. Further, if Generator terminates this Agreement after making payment(s) under this Agreement, Generator shall not receive a refund of any such payments made.
5.1.2 On or after the In-Service Date, in the event of the termination of the interconnection agreement between the Generator and the Transmission Provider entered in order to effectuate the interconnection described in the Recitals, the Generator may terminate this Agreement by giving SPC thirty (30) calendar days advance written notice of the termination of the interconnection agreement and Generator's election to terminate this Agreement; 5.1.3 The Generator shall be responsible for and pay to SPC all costs incurred by SPC for the SPC Work and any cancellation, penalty or similar costs relating to the cancellation of orders or contracts incurred by SPC because of Generator's decision to terminate this Agreement;
5.1.4 In the event of termination under this provision, the Parties shall use commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate the costs, damages and charges arising as a consequence of termination.
5.2 Right of SPC to Terminate - SPC shall have the right to terminate if an Event of Default has not been cured within the time periods set forth in Section 5.2.2.
5.2.1 Event of Default - An Event of Default shall mean: (a) Breach of the payment obligation by Generator pursuant to Section 7.3.
(b) Breach of any other material obligation of Generator under this Agreement.
In the event a default is not cured within the time periods under Section 5.2.2, SPC may take actions to terminate this Agreement, the Affected System Upgrades and all related services under this Agreement.
5.2.2 Right to Cure - For defaults under Section 5.2.1(a), Generator shall have thirty (30) days from the date the payment is due to cure the default. For defaults of Generator under Section 5.2.1(b), Generator shall have sixty (60) days from the first day of notice by SPC of the default to cure such default. SPC shall provide Generator with notice pursuant to Section 7.3 of such defaults within a reasonable time after SPC becomes aware that the default has occurred.
ARTICLE VI - INFORMATION REPORTING AND CONFIDENTIALITY
6.1 Information Reporting Obligations - Each Party shall, in accordance with Good Utility Practice, promptly provide to the other Parties all relevant information, documents or data regarding the Party's facilities and equipment which may reasonably be expected to pertain to the reliability of the other Party's facilities and equipment and which has been reasonably requested by the other Party.
6.2 Confidentiality - Confidential Information shall include, without limitation, all information relating to a Party's technology, research and development, business affairs, and enterprise, any other confidential, proprietary or commercially-sensitive information supplied by either of the Parties to the other, inclusive of any information supplied by a Party to another Party prior to the execution of this Agreement. Confidential information shall be maintained as confidential and shall not be disclosed (except as may be required by law, regulation, court of competent jurisdiction or Governmental Authority), except that SPC may disclose confidential information to transmission owners as may be needed for reliable operation of the electric system.
6.2.1 Term. During the term of this Agreement and for a period of three (3) years after the expiration or termination of this Agreement, except as otherwise provided in this Section.
6.2.2 Rights. Each Party retains all rights, title and interest in the Confidential Information that it discloses to the receiving Party. The disclosure by a party to the receiving Party of Confidential Information shall not be deemed a waiver by the disclosing Party or any other person or entity of the right to protect the Confidential Information from public disclosure.
6.2.3 No Warranties. By providing Confidential Information, neitther Party makes any warranties or representations as to its accuracy or completeness.
6.3 Disclosure Required by Law - If a court or Governmental Authority or entity with the right, power, and authority to do so requests or requires either Party, by subpoena, oral deposition, interrogatories, requests for production of documents, administrative order, or otherwise, to disclose Confidential Information, that Party shall provide the other Party with prompt notice of such request(s) or requirement(s) so that the other Party may seek, at that other Party's expense, an appropriate protective order. Notwithstanding the absence of a protective order or waiver, a Party may disclose such Confidential Information which, in the opinion of its counsel, the Party is legally compelled to disclose.
ARTICLE VII - BILLING AND PAYMENT AND CREDITWORTHINESS
7.1 Billing Procedures - Within thirty (30) days after the siging of this agreement, the Generator shall provide full payment of $400,000.00 in the form of cash or letter of credit. After construction is complete of the Affected System, SPC will do a true-up six (6) months after completion. If costs execede the estimated costs of $400,000.00, the Generator is responsible for paying the actual costs of the Affected System. If the costs are below the estimated costs of $400,000.00, SPC will provide re-payment within thrirty (30) days. All payments shall be made in immediately available funds payable to SPC, or by electronic funds (fed wire or ACH or similar electronic transfer means approved by SPC) to a designated bank account named by SPC. SPC's current designated bank account information is listed on Appendix B.
7.2 Interest on Unpaid Balances - In addition to any other rights or remedies, legal or equitable, available to SPC, interest on any unpaid amounts (other than on amounts paid in escrow under Section 7.3) shall be charged up to the maximum rate allowable under applicable law. Interest on delinquent amounts shall be calculated from the due date of the bill to the date of payment. When payments are made by mail, bills shall be considered as having been paid on the date of receipt by SPC.
7.3 Customer Payment Default - In the event Generator fails for any reason to make payment to SPC on or before the due date as described above, and such failure of payment is not cured within the time period specified in Section 5.2.2, a default by Generator shall be deemed to exist. In the event of a billing dispute between SPC and Generator, SPC will continue to provide all services under this Agreement as long as Generator tenders all payments in dispute to an independent escrow account in joint legal title of Generator and SPC at a mutually agreed financial institution pending resolution of the dispute. The interest earned on the escrow account shall be the only interest paid by either Party on unpaid balances while the funds are in escrow.
7.4 Creditworthiness Procedures - For the purpose of determining the ability of the Generator to meet its obligations related to this Agreement after the In-Service Date, SPC may require reasonable credit review of the Generator.
ARTICLE VIII - FORCE MAJEURE, INDEMNIFICATION AND LIMITATION ON LIABILITY
8.1 Force Majeure - Neither SPC nor Generator will be considered in default as to any obligation under this Agreement if prevented from fulfilling the obligation due to an event of Force Majeure. However, a Party whose performance under this Agreement is hindered by an event of Force Majeure shall make all reasonable efforts to perform its obligations under this Agreement. In no case shall a Force Majeure event excuse any payment obligation of Generator pursuant to this Agreement.
8.2 Indemnification - Generator shall at all times indemnify, defend and save SPC harmless from, any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demands, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from SPC's performance of its obligations under this Agreement on behalf of Generator, except in cases of gross negligence or intentional wrongdoing by SPC or SPC's contractors or sub-contractors. This indemnity shall not apply unless SPC gives Generator reasonable prior written notice of any claims, demands or actions. SPC shall have the right to defend such action and Generator shall have the right to participate in such defense. Generator shall have no liability hereunder for any settlement made without its prior written consent.
8.3 Limitation on Liability - Neither Party shall be liable to the other for any indirect, incidental, consequential, punitive, multiple, exemplary damages or lost profits arising out of, due to, or in connection with either Party's performance or nonperformance under this Agreement, or any of its obligations herein, whether based on contract, tort, strict liability, warranty or otherwise; provided, however, that nothing in this Section 8.3 shall limit or otherwise affect SPC's rights under Section 8.2 of this Agreement.
ARTICLE IX - REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES
9.1 Generator's Representations and Warranties - Generator represents and warrants that:
9.1.1 It is a limited liablity company validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the State of Delaware, and that it has all requisite power and authority to carry on the business to be conducted by it and to enter into this Agreement and shall maintain such status during the term of this Agreement. The execution and delivery of this Agreement and the performance of Generator's obligations hereunder have been duly authorized by appropriate Generator executive authority.
9.1.2 There is no threatened or pending action or proceeding affecting Generator before any court, governmental agency or arbitrator that could reasonably be expected to materially adversely affect the financial condition or operations of Generator in a manner that would impair the ability of Generator to perform its obligations hereunder or that purports to affect the legality, validity or enforceability of this Agreement.
9.2 SPC's Representations and Warranties - SPC represents and warrants that:
9.2.1 It is a corporation duly organized, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the State of Delaware and has all requisite corporate power and authority to carry on the business presently conducted by it and to enter into this Agreement and shall maintain such status during the term of this Agreement. The execution and delivery of this Agreement and the performance of SPC's obligations hereunder have been duly authorized by SPC and all necessary actions to consummate the transactions and actions contemplated hereunder have been taken.
9.2.2 There is no threatened or pending action or proceeding affecting SPC before any court, governmental agency or arbitrator that could reasonably be expected to materially adversely affect the financial condition or operations of SPC in a manner that would impair the ability of SPC to perform its obligations hereunder or that purports to affect the legality, validity or enforceability of this Agreement.
9.2.3 It has taken, or will take at the appropriate time, all necessary steps to obtain approval, if necessary, of this Agreement by RUS.
9.3 Representation of Both Parties - The representations and warranties in Section 9.1 and 9.2 shall continue in full force and effect for the term of this Agreement.
ARTICLE X - ASSIGNMENT
10.1 Consent to Assignment - Neither Party shall voluntarily assign its rights nor delegate its duties under this Agreement, or any part of such rights or duties, without the written consent of the other Party, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld. Any assignment or delegation made without such required written consent shall be null and void. In addition, notwithstanding the foregoing, either party may assign this Agreement without prior written consent of the other party, but upon providing written notice, to any wholly owned direct or indirect subsidiary or to any successor affiliate thereof.
10.2 Assignment to Facilitate Financing - Notwithstanding the provisions of Section 10.1, Generator may assign this Agreement to the persons, entities or institutions providing financing or refinancing for the development, design, construction or operation of the Affected System Upgrades and if Generator provides notice thereof to SPC, SPC shall provide notice and reasonable opportunity for such lenders to cure any default under this Agreement, provided, however, that the time to cure shall not be any greater than the time set forth in Section 5.2.2 hereof. If Generator makes such an assignment under this Section 10.2, Generator shall provide written notice to SPC within ten (10) days. Such notice shall include for such financing entity the information required under Section 12.7. SPC shall provide notice of any breaches or defaults to the financing entity at the same time pursuant to the terms of this Agreement. In the event of any foreclosure by such financing entity, the purchasers at such foreclosure or any subsequent purchaser shall, if they request, be entitled to the rights and benefits of (and be bound by the obligation and responsibility of) this Agreement, so long as they are determined by SPC to be an entity entitled to interconnect to the Transmission Provider, and agree to comply with all terms and conditions of this Agreement.
10.3 Successors and Assigns - Notwithstanding the foregoing, the provisions of this Agreement shall inure to the benefit of, and shall bind, the heirs, executors, administrators, successors and assigns of the respective Parties.
ARTICLE XI - TAXES
11.1 Generator Payments Not Taxable - The Parties intend that all payments or property transfers made by Generator to SPC for the installation of the Affected System Upgrades shall be non-taxable, either as contributions to capital, or as an advance, in accordance with the Internal Revenue Code and any applicable state income tax laws and shall not be taxable as contributions in aid of construction or otherwise under the Internal Revenue Code and any applicable state income tax laws.
11.2 Taxes Other Than Income Taxes - Upon the timely request by Generator, and at Generator's sole expense, SPC may appeal, protest, seek abatement of, or otherwise contest any tax (other than federal or state income tax) asserted or assessed against SPC for which Generator may be required to reimburse SPC under the terms of this Agreement. Generator shall pay to SPC on a periodic basis, as invoiced by SPC, SPC's documented reasonable costs of prosecuting such appeal, protest, abatement, or other contest. Generator and SPC shall cooperate in good faith with respect to any such contest. Unless the payment of such taxes is a prerequisite to an appeal or abatement or cannot be deferred, no amount shall be payable by Generator to SPC for such taxes until they are assessed by a final, non-appealable order by any court or agency of competent jurisdiction. In the event that a tax payment is withheld and ultimately due and payable after appeal, Generator will be responsible for all taxes, interest and penalties, other than penalties attributable to any delay caused by SPC.
11.3 Tax Status - Each Party shall cooperate with the other to maintain the other Party's tax status. Nothing in this Agreement is intended to adversely affect SPC's tax exempt status with respect to the issuance of bonds including, but not limited to, local furnishing bonds.
11.4 Indemnity of Tax Liability - Generator shall protect, indemnify and hold harmless SPC from all damages or consequences regarding any tax liability imposed against SPC as the result of this Agreement as well as any interest and penalties, other than interest and penalties attributable to a delay caused solely by SPC.
ARTICLE XII - OTHER PROVISIONS
12.1 Governing Law - This Agreement and the rights and duties of the Parties arising out of this Agreement shall be governed by, construed, enforced and performed in accordance with the applicable laws of the State of Alabama without regard to principles of conflicts of law.
12.2 Headings Not Affecting Meaning - The descriptive headings of the various Sections and Articles of the Agreement have been inserted for convenience of reference only and shall in no way modify or restrict any of the terms and provisions hereof.
12.3 Amendments - This Agreement may be amended by and only by a written instrument duly executed by each of the Parties hereto.
12.4 Waiver - Any waiver at any time by either Party of its rights with respect to a default under this Agreement, or with respect to any other matters arising in connection with this Agreement, shall not be deemed a waiver with respect to any subsequent default or other matter.
12.5 Good Utility Practice(s) - SPC and Generator shall discharge their respective obligations under this Agreement in accordance with Good Utility Practice(s).
12.6 Cooperation - Each Party to the Agreement shall reasonably and timely cooperate with the other as to all aspects relating to the performance of their respective obligations under the Agreement, in accordance with the terms hereof.
12.7 Notices - Any notice, demand or request required or permitted to be given by either Party to the other and any instrument required or permitted to be tendered or delivered by either Party to the other may be so given, tendered or delivered, as the case may be, by depositing the same in any United States Post Office Box with postage prepaid, for transmission by certified or registered mail, addressed to the Party, or personally delivered to the Party by hand or overnight delivery service, or by facsimile transmission followed by one of the preceding forms of delivery at the address set out below or such other address identified by the Party to the other Party in writing: To SPC: Southern Power Company 3535 Colonnade Parkway Birmingham, AL 35243 Attention: Transmission Manager
Phone: 205-992-0271 Email: g2spctrans@southernco.com
To Generator: Old Hayneville Solar, LLC Attn: Legal Department 130 Roberts St. Asheville, NC 28801 Email: legal@pgrenewables.com
12.8 RUS Approval - The effectiveness of this Agreement shall be dependent upon obtaining approval, if necessary, of RUS or of any other Governmental Authority having jurisdiction.
12.9 Non-liability for Certain Costs - SPC shall not be liable for any costs or damages due to the inability of Generator or its designated representatives to obtain any licenses or permits relating to Generator's responsibilities under this Agreement required by any Governmental Authority having jurisdiction over such matters.
12.10 Disclaimer - EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY SET FORTH HEREIN, SPC EXPRESSLY NEGATES ANY REPRESENTATION OR WARRANTY, WRITTEN OR ORAL, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, ANY REPRESENTATION OR WARRANTY WITH RESPECT TO CONFORMITY TO MODELS OR SAMPLES, OR MERCHANTABILITY OR FITNESS FOR ANY PARTICULAR PURPOSE. 12.11 Whole Agreement - This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement and understanding between the Parties hereto with reference to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior oral and written understandings and agreements between the Parties. No change or modification as to any of the provisions hereof shall be binding on either Party unless reduced to writing and approved by the authorized officer or agent of Generator and SPC. The terms and conditions of this Agreement and every Appendix referred to herein shall be amended, as agreed to by the Parties, to comply with changes or alterations made necessary by a valid applicable order of any Governmental Authority, or any court, having jurisdiction hereof. This Agreement may be executed in multiple original counterparts and any counterpart hereof having attached thereto the signatures of both Parties hereto (whether on one page or on separate pages) shall be deemed a fully executed original.
12.12 Independent Contractor Status - Nothing in the Agreement shall be construed as creating any relationship between Generator and SPC other than that of an independent contractor.
12.13 No Presumptions - This Agreement shall be construed without regard to any presumption or other rule requiring construction against the Party causing this Agreement to be drafted.
12.14 No Third Party Beneficiaries - This Agreement is for the sole benefit of the Parties hereto and no other person or entity shall be entitled to rely upon or receive any benefit from this Agreement or any provision hereof.
12.15 Invalidity - If any provisions of this Agreement or the application thereof to any person or circumstances shall, to any extent, be invalid or unenforceable, the remainder of this Agreement, or the application of such provision to persons or circumstances other than those as to which it is held invalid or unenforceable, shall not be affected thereby, and each provision of this Agreement shall be valid and be enforceable to the fullest extent permitted by law.
12.16 Appendices - Appendix A may need revision after the Effective Date, and the Parties will use reasonable efforts to complete such revision if necessary as soon as practicable. Upon the completion of any such revision by a Party after the date hereof, Appendix A shall be delivered to the other Party for its review and approval, which is not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed.
12.17 Conflicts - In the event of a conflict between the body of this Agreement and any attachment, appendix, or exhibit hereto, the terms and provisions of the body of this Agreement shall prevail and be deemed to be the final intent of the Parties.
12.18 No Transmission or Interconnection Service - SPC is not a transmission provider and is not undertaking hereunder to provide any service in connection with the provision of transmission or interconnection service. This Agreement relates solely to the reimbursement of actual costs incurred or to be incurred by SPC at the location of an interconnected generation facility on the generator side of an interconnection, and which facility is engaged solely in the wholesale supply of electric capacity, energy and ancillary services under market-based rate tariff authority granted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, so to address adverse impacts on such SPC System of Generator's Facility interconnection to the APC system. SPC has no obligation to provide any form of service or credit to or for the benefit of Generator in connection with the subject matter of this Agreement.
12.19 Survival - Upon the expiration or termination of this Agreement, the following Sections shall survive the expiration or termination of this Agreement, as indicated: (i) Article VII shall continue to the extent necessary to provide for billings and payments for all costs incurred hereunder, so long as the Generator Facilities remain interconnected to the Transmission Provider, and any final billings and payments pursuant to any termination of this Agreement; (ii) Section 3.3.1, in accordance with its terms; (iii) Article VI, in accordance with its terms; and (iv) Sections 3.2.2, 8.2, 8.3, 12.1, 12.9, and Article XI to the extent that SPC is at risk for any liabilities, claims, or damages that arise.
